Minister of Sport and Recreation Tokozile Xasa is expected to brief the media as  Banyana Banyana, Proteas and the Netball National Team are all representing the country in various events. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Minister of Sport and Recreation Tokozile Xasa is expected to brief the media as  Banyana Banyana, Proteas and the Netball National Team are all representing the country in various events. South African sports fans will also give their stars a heroes send-off as they leave the country to represent the nation at various events in England and France. READ: Rabada could be ready for World Cup The Proteas will open the tournament against hosts England at Lord's on 30 May. While the Netball team will take on Wales in an away pre-World Cup warm-up series in early July. Banyana Banyana will play Germany, Spain and China in Group B. 